  <title>
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">Tosepan Kalnemachtiloyan: &quot;La escuela de todos&quot;</narrative>
  </title>
  <description>
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">Tosepan Kalnemachtiloyan is a bilingual indigenous school in the Sierra de Puebla, initiated by the Tosepan Titataniske indigenous cooperative, as a response to the hard life of indigenous children in local schools. The purpose is to better serve bilingual indigenous children and improve their ability to adapt to the school context. To glimpse the possibility of which they pass through the basic school years, diminishing the repetition and the scholastic abandonment.</narrative>
  </description>
